{
  "text": "where \u03c5 \u2208 (0, 1/2] denotes the violation probability threshold which is a system design parameter controlling the desired level of conservatism. Remark that the SINR requirement \u03b3 k translates to an achievable target rate of R k = log 2 (1 + \u03b3 k ), under ergodic conditions on the channel [CITATION_1] . Therefore, the constraint (8) can also be read as a rate-outage probability constraint, ensuring that the transmission rate R k is achievable for the kth user with probability (at least) 1 \u2212 \u03c5. For the sake of notation, we denote the stochastic uncertain component of the CI constraint by",
